A few things to keep in mind:

1. Theft from your account, though rare is a threat.
2. If you retire from your work here and come back at a later date your account will remain valid.
3. The clerics of Zilchus tell us that gold not stored safely in the bank may be stripped upon reaching the Netherworld.
4. DO NOT MESS WITH THE TOKENS IN THE PERSISTENT TOOLBOXS IN YOUR INVENTORY! I can't stress that enough. The order that they are in is important. If you have more than one box, don't consolidate them to be helpful. Mess with them and you will lose stuff.

The Furnature Mercantile Guild Representative can be found to your right.

-Bank Staff

Merchant Tills
In Nordock Rogue and Bard characters may attempt to use Slight of Hand to steal a few coins from a vendor's purse. Simply click on this object and follow the conversation. However no reward comes without risk so note that there is a small chance of getting caught each time you try and as an illegal act if caught you face potential jail time from the guards. But a canny escape artist should be out in no time. Characters wishing to become more proficient at this should train in picking pockets. Success can only be met at each till once per reset and if discovered you cannot attempt on the same till again that reset.
